          <.heading2 margin="my-5" id="table-text-position">
            <.link patch={~p"/chelekom/docs/table/#table-text-position"}>
              Text position prop
            </.link>
          </.heading2>

          <.cp>
            The
            <.custom_inline_code>text_position</.custom_inline_code>
            function allows you to customize the alignment of text within the table component, supporting several alignment options. You can set the position using values like
            <.custom_inline_code>left</.custom_inline_code>
            to align text to the left,
            <.custom_inline_code>right</.custom_inline_code>
            to align text to the right, and
            <.custom_inline_code>center</.custom_inline_code>
            to center the text. For a justified text layout, use <.custom_inline_code>justify</.custom_inline_code>. Additionally, you can control text alignment based on content flow direction by using
            <.custom_inline_code>start</.custom_inline_code>
            or <.custom_inline_code>end</.custom_inline_code>. By default, the text is aligned to the left if no value is provided.
          </.cp>

