          <.heading2 margin="my-5" id="table-cols-border">
            <.link patch={~p"/chelekom/docs/table/#table-cols-border"}>
              Cols border prop
            </.link>
          </.heading2>

          <.cp>
            The
            <.custom_inline_code>cols_border</.custom_inline_code>
            attribute sets the border style for columns in the table. You can customize the column borders by assigning specific styles like <.custom_inline_code>extra_small</.custom_inline_code>, <.custom_inline_code>small</.custom_inline_code>, or
            <.custom_inline_code>medium</.custom_inline_code>
            to adjust the thickness. If no value is provided, the default is <.custom_inline_code>nil</.custom_inline_code>, which results in no column borders being applied. This flexibility allows for more refined control over the table’s layout and presentation.
          </.cp>

