          <.heading2 margin="my-5" id="table-fixed">
            <.link patch={~p"/chelekom/docs/table/#table-fixed"}>
              Table fixed prop
            </.link>
          </.heading2>

          <.cp>
            The
            <.custom_inline_code>table_fixed</.custom_inline_code>
            prop adds the
            <.custom_inline_code>table-fixed</.custom_inline_code>
            Tailwind CSS class to the table. This class ensures that the table adheres to fixed column widths, where the width of the first row dictates the widths of all columns throughout the table. This setup is particularly useful for maintaining a consistent layout, as you can manually assign widths to specific columns while the remaining width is distributed evenly among columns without explicit widths.
          </.cp>

